{{DISPLAYTITLE:A_VolcBallImpact}}
'''A_VolcBallImpact'''<br>
(no parameter)<br>

If the calling actor is under the floor, it is raised by 28 units and given the NOGRAVITY flag. (This is presumably a leftover from a hack used by Raven Software to work around their terrain clipping bug, the same that was responsible for the [[CVARs:Configuration#compat_minotaur|minotaur floorfire bug]].)

This creates a small explosion, equivalent to [[A_Explode]](25, 25, true) that deals fire damage. The calling actor's target, if any, is considered responsible for the damage inflicted. It then spawns four {{Class|VolcanoTBlast}} actors and sends them on each cardinal direction with a horizontal velocity of 0.7 and a random vertical velocity between 0 and 2.

This codepointer is restricted to {{Class|VolcanoBlast}} and derived classes.

